cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.MM

This paper is primarily focused on computer vision, specifically on learning visual features from weakly-labeled image collections. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). However, the paper also discusses the use of captions and word similarity, which suggests that it could also be relevant to sub-categories such as cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Additionally, the use of convolutional networks and large datasets suggests that it could be relevant to sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.MM (Multimedia).
